File: A laboratory assistant works on a test sample of a suspected case of the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - Twenty-eight health officials have tested positive for COVID-19 in Gauteng. The Gauteng department of health says most cases were mild and did not require hospitalisation, except for one employee who has since been discharged. READ: Ramaphosa expected to announce eased lockdown conditions The department says the health officials were infected through social circles and not at the workplace, where they have a sufficient supply of personal protective equipment. However, some nurses have threatened a stay away because they say PPEs (Personal protective equipment) are in short supply. Gauteng has just over 1,200 confirmed COVID-19 cases, which is the highest in the country. More than 1,000 people have recovered from the virus in South Africa. Gauteng Results District Br... by eNCA.com on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.